{"title_page": "Benard Odoh", "text_new": "{{short description|Nigerian politician}}\n{{Use Nigerian English|date=November 2019}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n'''Benard Ifeanyi Odoh''' is a [[Nigerians|Nigerian]] politician. Odoh was appointed the Secretary of [[Ebonyi State]] Government by [[Dave Umahi]] (the Governor of Ebonyi State) but left office by resignation in 2018.<ref name=\":0\" />{{Infobox office holder\n| name                = \n| office              = Secretary to the State Government\n| order               = Ebonyi State Cabinet\n| termstart           = 31 May 2015\n| termend             = 3 April 2018\n| appointer           = [[Dave Umahi]]\n| successor           = Hyginus Nwokwu\n| image               = \n| state               = Ebonyi State\n| party               = [[All Progressives Congress]]\n| nationality         = [[Nigerian]]\n| website             = {{url|BenardOdoh.com}}\n| education           = [[Nnamdi Azikiwe University]], Awka\n| parents             = Joseph Odoh\n| spouse              = Juliana Nkechi Odoh\n}}\n\n== Political career ==\nOdoh began his political career when he ran for Senate under the [[All Progressives Grand Alliance|All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA)]] but lost to Senator Obinna Ogba who ran under the [[People's Democratic Party (Nigeria)|People's Democratic Party]] platform in the 2015 general elections.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://thenationonlineng.net/ebonyi-ssg-prof-odoh-resigns/|title=Ebonyi SSG, Prof Odoh resigns|date=2018-04-02|website=The Nation Newspaper|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> Odoh then was appointed the [[Secretary to the State Government]] of Ebonyi State on May 2015 to by Governor [[Dave Umahi]] of Ebonyi State.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://thesightnews.com/see-former-ebonyi-state-ssg-prof-benard-odoh-resigned/ |title=See Why former Ebonyi State SSG, Prof. Benard Odoh Resigned |date=3 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.govserv.org/NG/Abakaliki/646541728817644/Prof.-Benard-Odoh |title=Prof. Benard Odoh, 25 Amagu Street, off Ezza Road, Abakaliki, Ebonyi State, Abakaliki (2019) |website=govserv.org |access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pressreader.com/nigeria/thisday/20150531/282681865861436 |title=PressReader.com \u2013 Your favorite newspapers and magazines |website=pressreader.com |access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref> He left his office by resignation on April 2018 and later joined the [[All Progressives Congress]] political party.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wawa.com.ng/orji-kalu-celebrates-prof-benard-odoh-as-the-first-and-youngest-to-obtain-apc-governorship-form-photos/|title=ORJI KALU CELEBRATES PROF BENARD ODOH AS THE FIRST AND YOUNGEST TO OBTAIN APC GOVERNORSHIP FORM {Photos}|last=Reporter|first=Wawa|date=2018-09-06|website=wawa|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-08}}</ref>  \n\nIn 2019 Odoh was a candidate during the gubernatorial elections in Ebonyi State on the [[All Progressives Congress]] platform but lost in the primaries to [[Sonni Ogbuoji]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theeagleonline.com.ng/2019-prof-odoh-rejects-apc-governorship-primary-result/amp/|title=2019: Prof. Odoh rejects APC governorship primary result {{!}} The Eagle Online|website=theeagleonline.com.ng|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punchng.com/ogbuoji-wins-ebonyi-apc-gov-primary-election/|title=Ogbuoji wins Ebonyi APC gov primary election|last=Published|website=Punch Newspapers|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Odoh, Benard}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Igbo politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Ebonyi State]] \n[[Category:Nigerian politicians]]\n[[Category:Secretaries to the State Government]]\n\n{{Nigeria-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nigerian politician}}\n{{Use Nigerian English|date=November 2019}}\n\n{{Use dmy 